### Component Specifications

#### LOI Control Bar
- **Position**: Directly below the editor header bar, full width
- **Height**: Auto (expands to fit content, ~140px when expanded)
- **Background**: `#F9FAFB`, bottom border 1px `#E5E7EB`
- **Collapsible**: Chevron on the right of the "Survey Length" label. Collapsed state shows just the slider and current LOI estimate in a single row (~48px height). Expanded state shows the full panel with focus note and stats.
- **Default**: Expanded on first visit, remembers collapsed state

#### LOI Slider
- **Type**: Range input (continuous), width ~100% of control bar content area (with left/right padding)
- **Snap points**: Three labeled tick marks at Quick (left), Standard (center), Deep (right). Slider snaps to these when within 10% proximity, but can rest between them.
- **Thumb**: 20px circle, `#2563EB`, white border 2px, shadow
- **Track**: 6px height, filled portion `#2563EB`, unfilled `#E5E7EB`, rounded
- **Tick labels**: Above the track. Icon + tier name + time range. Active snap point is `#2563EB` bold, others are `#6B7280`.
- **Current LOI display**: Below slider, centered on thumb position: "current: ~10 min" â€” 14px semibold `#2563EB`

#### Focus Note Box
- **Position**: Below slider
- **Background**: `#F0F9FF`, border 1px `#BFDBFE`, border-radius 8px, padding 12px
- **Content**: Changes dynamically as slider moves. Format:
  - **Tier label + description** of what this configuration prioritizes (1 sentence)
  - **"Drops:"** list of what's excluded compared to the next tier up
- **Transition**: Content fades/crossfades when slider moves between tiers (200ms)

#### Stats Row
- **Position**: Below focus note
- **Content**: "X of Y questions shown | Z hidden | N pinned by you | M excluded by you"
- **Style**: 13px, `#6B7280`, pipe-separated

#### Question Visibility States (in Editor Canvas)

Each question card now has a visibility state:

| State | Badge | Card Appearance | Actions |
|-------|-------|----------------|---------|
| Visible (included by LOI) | â— green dot | Normal â€” full card, fully editable | Pin, Exclude, Edit, Reorder, Delete |
| Hidden (excluded by LOI) | â—‹ gray dot | Collapsed â€” single row, gray text, muted | Pin to include, Expand to preview |
| Pinned (user override â€” always visible) | ğŸ“Œ blue pin icon | Normal + blue left border accent | Unpin, Edit, Reorder, Delete |
| Excluded (user override â€” always hidden) | ğŸš« red circle | Collapsed + strikethrough title | Un-exclude |

**Visible questions**: Rendered as normal question cards (same as Phase 3 spec). Show a small "Priority: required/recommended/optional" tag in muted text. Show Pin and Exclude icon buttons alongside the existing action buttons.

**Hidden questions**: Rendered as a single collapsed row:
```
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚  â—‹  Q12. Competitive pricing comparison   [recommended]      â”‚
â”‚     Hidden at current LOI                                    â”‚
â”‚                                  [ğŸ“Œ Pin to include] [â–¼ Expand]â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
```
- Background: `#F9FAFB`, border 1px `#E5E7EB` dashed, text `#9CA3AF`
- "Pin to include" adds the question back despite LOI setting
- "Expand" shows the full question card for preview (read-only at this state unless user pins it)

**Pinned questions**: Normal card + left border 3px `#2563EB` + small ğŸ“Œ badge top-right. These stay visible even if the user slides LOI below their priority level.

**Excluded questions**: Collapsed row + strikethrough title text + ğŸš« badge. These stay hidden even if the user slides LOI above their priority level.

#### Section Nav Updates
- Each question in the sidebar shows its visibility icon (â—/â—‹/ğŸ“Œ/ğŸš«)
- Hidden questions shown in lighter text `#D1D5DB`
- Section question counts update: "Pricing (4/6)" meaning 4 of 6 questions visible

### LOI Calculation Logic

```
For each slider position (0-100 scale):
  0-20:   Quick tier â€” include only `required` questions
  20-50:  Quickâ†’Standard interpolation â€” add `recommended` questions 
          sorted by methodology importance (most critical first)
  50:     Standard snap point â€” all `required` + all `recommended`
  50-80:  Standardâ†’Deep interpolation â€” add `optional` questions
          sorted by methodology importance
  80-100: Deep tier â€” all questions included

User overrides:
  Pinned questions: ALWAYS included regardless of slider position
  Excluded questions: NEVER included regardless of slider position

LOI estimate = sum of estimated_seconds for all visible questions + pinned
             - sum of estimated_seconds for excluded questions
             (converted to minutes, rounded to nearest 0.5)
```

### Focus Note Content Per Tier

| Tier | Focus Note | Drops (vs. next tier up) |
|------|-----------|--------------------------|
| Quick | "Fast validation on your core hypothesis. Includes screener and essential metrics only." | "Drops: diagnostic batteries, open-ends, secondary metrics, detailed demographics" |
| Standard | "Balanced depth for most studies. Includes screener, core metrics, and key diagnostics." | "Drops: extended open-ends, secondary attribute batteries, detailed competitive comparison" |
| Deep | "Maximum diagnostic depth for complex decisions. Every question included." | (nothing dropped) |
| Between Quickâ†’Standard | "Adding diagnostic depth. Core metrics plus [next question being added]." | Dynamic â€” shows which questions are next to be added/removed |
| Between Standardâ†’Deep | "Near-full depth. Adding [next question being added] for additional context." | Dynamic |

### Data Model Updates

Each question in `survey_output.json` gains:

```json
{
  "id": "string",
  "text": "string",
  "type": "string",
  "priority": "required | recommended | optional",
  "priority_rank": "number (1-N, ordering within priority level for interpolation)",
  "loi_visibility": "visible | hidden",
  "user_override": "none | pinned | excluded",
  "estimated_seconds": "number"
}
```

New top-level field:

```json
{
  "loi_config": {
    "slider_position": "number (0-100)",
    "snap_point": "quick | standard | deep | custom",
    "estimated_loi_minutes": "number",
    "total_questions": "number",
    "visible_questions": "number",
    "hidden_questions": "number",
    "user_pinned_count": "number",
    "user_excluded_count": "number"
  }
}
```

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Slider renders with three snap points and continuous movement between them
- [ ] Moving the slider instantly shows/hides questions in the editor canvas
- [ ] Focus note updates dynamically as slider moves
- [ ] LOI estimate updates in real time
- [ ] Stats row shows correct counts (visible/hidden/pinned/excluded)
- [ ] Hidden questions render as collapsed rows with "Pin to include" action
- [ ] Pinning a hidden question makes it visible with blue accent
- [ ] Excluding a visible question collapses and strikes it through
- [ ] Unpinning/un-excluding restores default LOI-based visibility
- [ ] Section nav sidebar reflects visibility states with icons and counts
- [ ] Slider position persists when navigating away and back
- [ ] Each hero skill produces meaningfully different question sets across Quick/Standard/Deep (not just truncation â€” different questions appear/disappear, not just the last N)

### Task Breakdown

| # | Task | Est. Effort | Notes |
|---|------|-------------|-------|
| 2.1 | Add priority + priority_rank tags to all 10 skills | 2 days | Tag every question block; define ordering within tiers |
| 2.2 | Implement LOI calculation engine | 1 day | Slider position â†’ visible question set, with interpolation logic |
| 2.3 | Build LOI slider component (snap points, continuous, labels) | 1 day | |
| 2.4 | Build LOI control bar (collapsible panel with focus note + stats) | 0.5 days | |
| 2.5 | Build dynamic focus note content (per tier + interpolation states) | 0.5 days | |
| 2.6 | Implement question visibility states in editor canvas (visible/hidden/pinned/excluded) | 1.5 days | 4 visual states per question card |
| 2.7 | Build Pin/Exclude toggle buttons on question cards | 0.5 days | |
| 2.8 | Build collapsed hidden question row with "Pin to include" and "Expand" | 0.5 days | |
| 2.9 | Update section nav sidebar with visibility icons and counts | 0.5 days | |
| 2.10 | Wire LOI recalculation to all edit operations (add/remove/pin/exclude) | 0.5 days | |
| 2.11 | Test across all 3 tiers Ã— 3 hero skills | 1 day | Verify meaningful differentiation |

