## Phase 4: Test / Preview Function

### Objective
Allow users to preview the survey exactly as a respondent would experience it, AND annotate questions with comments during the preview. After completing the preview, comments are summarised and the user can select which ones to send to the AI for targeted survey edits.

### Core Operations (Must Have)

1. **Respondent-view rendering** â€” Survey displays one question at a time (or one section at a time, configurable)
2. **Skip logic execution** â€” Selecting an answer that triggers skip logic actually skips
3. **Progress bar** â€” Shows respondent progress through the survey
4. **Navigation** â€” Next/Back buttons, question validation (required questions enforced)
5. **Comment on any question** â€” Floating comment button per question, opens a note panel
6. **End screen** â€” Shows completion message + comment summary
7. **Comment review & AI edit flow** â€” User selects which comments to action, AI makes targeted updates

### Not in MVP
- Simulated response data generation
- Device preview (mobile/tablet/desktop frames)
- Accessibility audit
- Timing measurement during preview
- Shareable preview link
- Multiple preview modes (page-by-page vs. all-at-once)

### UI Layout Specification

