### Component Specifications

#### Preview Header
- **Background**: `#FEF3C7` (amber-100) â€” visually distinct from the editor to make it clear this is preview mode
- **Height**: 48px
- **Left**: Warning icon + "PREVIEW MODE" in semibold amber text
- **Center**: Survey title (read-only)
- **Right**: "Exit Preview" button with Ã— icon

#### Progress Bar
- **Position**: Below header, full width of content area
- **Height**: 8px bar + 16px label below
- **Bar**: Background `#E5E7EB`, fill `#2563EB`, rounded
- **Label**: "Q3 of 12" right-aligned, 14px, gray

#### Question Display Area
- **Container**: White, max-width 640px, centered, padding 40px, border-radius 12px, subtle shadow
- **Question number**: 16px semibold gray
- **Question text**: 20px regular, color `#111827`, margin-bottom 24px
- **Response options**: Rendered faithfully per question type:
  - **Single select**: Radio buttons with labels, 16px, 12px gap between options
  - **Multi select**: Checkboxes
  - **Open end**: Text input or textarea
  - **Grid**: HTML table with radio buttons at intersections
  - **Ranking**: Numbered list with up/down buttons (simplified)
  - **Slider**: Range input with min/max labels
  - **Rating scale**: Horizontal radio group with scale labels
- **Navigation**: Back/Next buttons, right-aligned. Next is primary style, Back is secondary. Next is disabled until required question answered.

#### Comment Button & Panel
- **Comment button**: "ğŸ’¬ Add Comment" â€” positioned bottom-right of question display area. Secondary style, small. If question already has a comment, shows "ğŸ’¬ 1 comment" with count badge.
- **Comment panel**: Slides in from the right side of the question display area (or appears below it on smaller screens).
  - **Background**: White, border 1px `#E5E7EB`, border-radius 8px, padding 16px, shadow
  - **Header**: "ğŸ’¬ Comment on Q3" â€” 14px semibold
  - **Textarea**: 3 rows, auto-expanding, placeholder "Add your notes about this question..."
  - **Save button**: "Save Comment" â€” small primary button. On save, textarea clears and comment appears in "Previous comments" list below.
  - **Previous comments**: Chronological list. Each comment shows text + timestamp + [Edit] [Delete] icons.
  - **Close**: Click outside or Ã— button to collapse panel

#### Comment Data Model (Per Question)

```json
{
  "question_id": "string",
  "comments": [
    {
      "id": "string (uuid)",
      "text": "string",
      "created_at": "datetime",
      "theme": "string (assigned during summarisation)"
    }
  ]
}
```

#### Editor Notes Panel (Preview-only)
- **Position**: Below question display (and below comment panel if open)
- **Background**: `#F0F9FF` (blue-50), border 1px `#BFDBFE`, border-radius 8px, padding 16px
- **Content**: Shows skip logic rules active on this question, priority tag, estimated time.
- **Visibility**: Only shown in preview mode â€” respondents would never see this

#### Comment Summary & AI Edit Flow (Completion Screen)

**Comment Summary Cards**:
- AI groups raw comments into 2-5 themes using an LLM summarisation call
- Each theme card:
  - **Header**: Theme icon + label (e.g., "ğŸ”„ Scale adjustments") + comment count â€” 14px semibold
  - **Body**: Summarised version of the grouped comments, with original question references â€” 14px regular `#374151`
  - **Checkbox**: "Include in AI edit" â€” bottom right. Checked by default for all themes.
  - **Container**: White, border 1px `#E5E7EB`, border-radius 8px, padding 16px, margin-bottom 12px
  - **Expand**: Click to expand and see original raw comments (collapsed by default, showing only the summary)

**Additional Instructions**:
- Single-line text input below the theme cards
- Placeholder: "e.g., 'Keep the total LOI under 10 minutes'"
- Optional â€” user can leave blank

**Action Buttons**:
- "Apply Selected Edits with AI â†’" â€” primary, full width. Sends selected themes + additional instructions to the AI for targeted survey updates.
- "Return to Editor Without Changes" â€” secondary text link below

**AI Edit Progress**:
- Same pattern as generation progress (step list with status icons)
- Steps reflect the specific edits being applied

**Diff View**:
- After AI completes edits, show a per-question diff of what changed
- Each diff card:
  - Question number + short label
  - BEFORE state (gray text, strikethrough or faded)
  - AFTER state (normal text, green left border accent)
  - [âœ“ Accept] / [âœ— Reject] buttons per change
- Bottom: "Accept All & Return to Editor" (primary) / "Reject All & Return to Editor" (secondary)
- Partially accepting: User can accept some, reject others. On clicking "Return to Editor", only accepted changes are applied.

#### Completion Screen (No Comments Path)
If the user completes the preview without adding any comments, show a simpler completion screen:

```
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚                                          â”‚
â”‚        âœ… Preview Complete               â”‚
â”‚                                          â”‚
â”‚   12 questions reviewed                  â”‚
â”‚   Estimated respondent time: 9 min       â”‚
â”‚                                          â”‚
â”‚   Skip logic triggered:                  â”‚
â”‚   â€¢ Q3 â†’ Skipped Q4-Q7 (concept reject) â”‚
â”‚                                          â”‚
â”‚   No comments added.                     â”‚
â”‚                                          â”‚
â”‚        [Return to Editor]                â”‚
â”‚                                          â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
```

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All question types render correctly in respondent view
- [ ] Skip logic executes correctly (selecting a trigger option advances to the correct question)
- [ ] Progress bar updates accurately (accounts for skipped questions)
- [ ] Required question validation prevents advancing without answer
- [ ] Back button works and preserves previous answers
- [ ] Comment button appears on every question, opens comment panel
- [ ] Comments can be added, edited, and deleted per question
- [ ] Comment count badge updates on the comment button
- [ ] Completion screen shows AI-grouped comment summary with theme cards
- [ ] User can check/uncheck themes for AI editing
- [ ] User can add additional instructions for the AI
- [ ] "Apply Selected Edits" triggers AI edit with progress display
- [ ] Diff view shows before/after for each changed question
- [ ] User can accept/reject individual changes
- [ ] Accepted changes are applied to the survey when returning to editor
- [ ] Rejected changes are discarded
- [ ] No-comments path shows simple completion screen
- [ ] Editor notes panel shows correct metadata per question
- [ ] Exit preview returns to editor in the correct state

### Task Breakdown

| # | Task | Est. Effort | Notes |
|---|------|-------------|-------|
| 4.1 | Build preview page shell (header, progress, content area) | 0.5 days | |
| 4.2 | Build question renderers for each type | 2 days | 9 question types Ã— rendering |
| 4.3 | Implement skip logic engine | 1 day | Walk the question list respecting conditions |
| 4.4 | Build navigation (next/back) with validation | 0.5 days | |
| 4.5 | Build comment button + comment panel (slide-in) | 1 day | Per-question comments with CRUD |
| 4.6 | Build editor notes panel | 0.25 days | |
| 4.7 | Build completion screen (with and without comments) | 0.5 days | |
| 4.8 | Build comment summarisation LLM call (group into themes) | 1 day | Prompt engineering for theme grouping |
| 4.9 | Build comment summary UI (theme cards with checkboxes) | 0.5 days | |
| 4.10 | Build "Apply Edits" AI call + progress display | 1 day | Targeted edit prompt from selected themes |
| 4.11 | Build diff view (before/after per question with accept/reject) | 1.5 days | Most complex UI in this phase |
| 4.12 | Wire accepted changes back into survey JSON | 0.5 days | |
| 4.13 | Test with hero skill outputs (pricing, message, concept) | 1 day | Validate all types render + comment â†’ edit flow works |

---

## Phase 5: Reporting Function

### Objective
Show what the output of a fielded survey looks like. For the partnership demo, this will use pre-seeded realistic data. The reporting must look like something a CMO would put in front of their board.

### Core Features (Must Have)

1. **Summary dashboard** â€” Key metrics at a glance (sample size, field dates, LOI actual vs. estimated, completion rate)
2. **Question-level results** â€” Chart + data table for every question
3. **Cross-tabulation** â€” Filter/break results by one demographic variable (e.g., age, gender)
4. **Statistical significance** â€” Flag significant differences in cross-tabs (at 95% confidence)
5. **AI-generated insights** â€” 3-5 bullet summary of key findings, generated per question and overall
6. **Export** â€” Download as PDF or PowerPoint

### Not in MVP
- Real-time data streaming (data is pre-seeded)
- Custom filtering/pivot tables
- Raw data CSV export
- Advanced stats (regression, factor analysis, cluster analysis)
- Dashboard customization / saved views
- Multi-wave comparison

