**Note for implementation**: The status page is fully stubbed for MVP. The progress bar and metrics can animate/increment on a timer to simulate live fielding during a demo. "View Interim Results" navigates to the Reporting page with partial seed data.

### Component Specifications

#### Step Indicator
- **Layout**: Horizontal stepper, three circles connected by lines
- **Active step**: Filled circle `#2563EB`, bold label
- **Completed step**: Filled circle `#10B981` (green) with checkmark
- **Future step**: Outlined circle `#D1D5DB`, gray label

#### Audience Configuration
- **Country selector**: Single dropdown, default US
- **Demographics**: Checkbox groups in a 2-column grid. Each group has a "Select All" toggle.
- **Screening criteria**: Auto-populated card showing conditions derived from the survey's screener questions. Read-only display with link to edit in survey editor.

#### Sample & Budget
- **Sample size**: Input field with preset buttons (200, 400, 600, 1000, Custom). Clicking a preset fills the input.
- **Stats guidance box**: Dynamically updates based on sample size. Shows margin of error, sub-group reliability note.
- **Quotas table**: Simple table with Variable, Target (Natural/Custom), Distribution columns. Natural = census-proportional.
- **Cost estimate box**: Calculated from `sample_size Ã— CPI + platform_fee`. CPI can be hardcoded for MVP ($3-5 range). Show line items.

#### Review & Launch
- **Summary**: Clean key-value list of all configured parameters
- **Pre-launch checklist**: Three checkbox items. All should be checked before launch button enables (or just advisory for MVP).
- **Launch button**: Large, primary style, with rocket icon. Click triggers confirmation modal: "Are you sure you want to launch this study? Estimated cost: $1,600" with Cancel / Confirm buttons.

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] 3-step wizard flows correctly (next/back navigation, step indicator updates)
- [ ] Audience configuration captures country, demographics, shows auto-populated screener criteria
- [ ] Sample size selection updates margin of error and cost estimate dynamically
- [ ] Quota table displays with sensible defaults
- [ ] Review screen accurately reflects all settings from steps 1-2
- [ ] Launch confirmation modal appears and "launches" (transitions to status page)
- [ ] Status page renders with simulated progress (animated or timer-based for demo)

### Task Breakdown

| # | Task | Est. Effort | Notes |
|---|------|-------------|-------|
| 6.1 | Build step wizard shell (indicator, navigation, step transitions) | 0.5 days | Reusable 3-step component |
| 6.2 | Build Step 1: Audience configuration | 1 day | Country, demographics, screener display |
| 6.3 | Build Step 2: Sample & budget | 1 day | Sample presets, MoE calc, cost estimate |
| 6.4 | Build Step 3: Review & launch | 0.5 days | Summary display, checklist, confirm modal |
| 6.5 | Build post-launch status page (stubbed) | 0.5 days | Simulated progress animation |
| 6.6 | Wire screener auto-population from survey data | 0.5 days | Parse screener section of survey JSON |
| 6.7 | End-to-end test: editor â†’ launch â†’ status | 0.5 days | |

---

## Summary: Effort Estimates

| Phase | Description | Estimated Days |
|-------|-------------|----------------|
| 1 | Survey Skills (10 use cases) | 12-14 |
| 2 | LOI Slider Functionality | 9-10 |
| 3 | Edit Function | 7-8 |
| 4 | Test / Preview + Comments + AI Edit Loop | 10-12 |
| 5 | Reporting Function | 12-14 |
| 6 | Launch Function | 4-5 |
| â€” | **Total** | **54-63 days** |

Note: Setup page and navigation are specced in the companion document (setup-and-navigation.md) and add ~9 days, bringing the full build to **63-72 working days**.

### Risk Notes

- **Reporting is the heaviest UI phase** â€” specialty charts (Van Westendorp, Gabor-Granger) and cross-tab rendering are the most complex UI components. Consider using a charting library with good line-chart support (Recharts, Plotly, Nivo).
- **LOI slider interpolation logic** is the trickiest algorithmic piece â€” the mapping from slider position to visible question set needs to feel smooth and intentional, not random. Invest time in getting the `priority_rank` ordering right per skill so the interpolation reveals questions in a logical sequence.
- **Comment â†’ AI edit loop** has two LLM calls in sequence (summarisation, then targeted edit) â€” latency could feel slow if not handled well. Consider streaming the progress steps. The diff view is the most complex UI in Phase 4.
- **Seed data quality matters** â€” unrealistic data will undermine demo credibility. Invest time in making seed data statistically coherent (percentages sum to 100, cross-tab distributions are plausible, significance tests align with visible differences).
- **Export (PDF/PPTX) is deceptively time-consuming** â€” consider deprioritizing PPTX export to post-MVP if time pressure increases. PDF is sufficient for the demo.
- **Multi-skill selection** is the riskiest part of Phase 1 â€” a brief that requires both pricing AND concept testing must produce a coherent integrated survey, not two surveys stapled together.

### Demo Script Suggestion

For the Previously Unavailable demo, walk through:
1. **Paste a brief**: "We're launching a new DTC skincare serum..." â€” paste the whole paragraph
2. **Watch extraction**: AI pulls out objective, audience, competitors, category in 5 seconds
3. **Review & refine**: Quick glance at extracted fields, adjust one thing, hit Generate
4. **Show the AI generating** a pricing + concept study in seconds
5. **Play with the LOI slider**: Drag from Deep to Quick â€” watch questions appear/disappear. "This is a 20-minute survey... now it's 5 minutes, and it still covers pricing fundamentals." Pin one optional question back in.
6. **Make a couple of edits** in the editor â€” change a response option, tweak wording
7. **Preview the survey** â€” walk through 4-5 questions, drop a comment on Q3 ("scale feels too granular")
8. **Comment summary + AI edit**: At the end, select the comment theme, hit "Apply Edits" â€” watch the AI fix Q3's scale
9. **Accept the diff** â€” one click, back in the editor with the fix applied
10. **Go to Launch** â€” configure audience, see cost estimate
11. **Jump to Reporting** (pre-seeded) â€” show the Van Westendorp chart, cross-tabs by age, AI insights
12. **Export to PDF**

Total demo time: ~12 minutes. Punchline: "What just took 12 minutes â€” including reviewing and refining the AI's work â€” would take a research agency 3-4 weeks and $25-40K."


# Setup Page & Navigation Architecture
## Companion to MVP Build Plan

