### Component Specifications

#### Page Title Area
- **Max width**: 720px, centered horizontally with 32px side padding
- **Title**: State 1: "Start Your Study" / State 2: "Review Your Brief" â€” 28px semibold, `#111827`
- **Subtitle**: 16px regular, `#6B7280` â€” changes per state

#### STATE 1 Components

**Brief Textarea**:
- Height: 12 rows minimum, auto-expands as user types (max 24 rows before scroll)
- Border: 1px `#D1D5DB`, border-radius 8px
- Focus: Border `#2563EB`, ring `0 0 0 2px rgba(37,99,235,0.2)`
- Placeholder: Multi-line example brief (see wireframe above) â€” 14px `#9CA3AF`
- Value text: 16px `#111827`
- Padding: 16px

**Brief File Upload**:
- Positioned below textarea, separated by an "â”€â”€ OR â”€â”€" divider (centered text, horizontal lines either side, 13px `#9CA3AF`)
- Container: Dashed border 2px `#D1D5DB`, border-radius 8px, padding 20px, text-centered
- Accepts: PDF, .docx, .txt files. On upload, file content is extracted and populates the textarea above (replacing the upload area with a file chip showing filename + "Content extracted âœ“")
- Drag hover state: Border `#2563EB`, background `#EFF6FF`

**Extract Brief Button**:
- Style: Large primary button, full width of content area (720px max), height 52px
- Label: "Extract Brief â†’" â€” 16px semibold white
- Background: `#2563EB`, hover `#1D4ED8`
- Disabled state: When textarea is empty â€” `#D1D5DB` background, `#9CA3AF` text

**Manual Entry Link**:
- Below the Extract button: "I'd rather fill in the fields manually â†“" â€” 14px text link, `#2563EB`, underline on hover
- Clicking this skips extraction and shows State 2 with all fields empty

**Extraction Progress**:
- Replaces the Extract button area while running
- Container: White, border 1px `#E5E7EB`, border-radius 12px, padding 24px, centered
- Spinner + "Reading your brief..." text
- Progress bar: 8px height, indeterminate animation (or step-based if extraction has distinct phases)
- Typically completes in 3-8 seconds

#### STATE 2 Components (Review & Refine)

**Transition**: State 1 smoothly transitions to State 2. The textarea collapses into the "Original Brief" collapsible banner, and the structured fields animate in below. Alternatively, a simple page-level swap is acceptable for MVP.

**Original Brief Banner**:
- **Position**: Top of State 2, below page title
- **Background**: `#F9FAFB`, border 1px `#E5E7EB`, border-radius 8px, padding 16px
- **Default state**: Collapsed â€” shows "ğŸ“‹ Original Brief" label + first ~80 chars of brief text, truncated with ellipsis. Chevron on right.
- **Expanded state**: Full brief text visible (max-height 200px, scroll if longer)
- **Actions**: 
  - "Re-extract" â€” re-runs extraction with the original text (useful if user edits the original)
  - "Edit original" â€” expands the brief text into an editable textarea within the banner. Saving triggers re-extraction.

**AI-Populated Field Indicator** `[âœ¨ AI]`:
- Small badge shown on the right side of each field label that was populated by extraction
- Style: 12px, `#8B5CF6` (purple) text, no background â€” just a subtle marker
- Purpose: Signals "this was filled by AI â€” double-check it"
- Disappears once the user manually edits the field (indicating they've reviewed it)
- Not shown on fields the user fills manually or that extraction left empty

**Form Sections** (in State 2):
- Same layout as previously specified but all start **expanded** (not collapsed) since they may contain extracted data
- Sections with no extracted data show the field with placeholder text â€” user can fill or leave empty
- **Required fields**: Study Name, Research Objective, Category, Target Audience, Market â€” marked with red asterisk (*)
- **Optional fields**: Stimulus, Competitors, Specific Questions â€” clearly labeled "(optional)"

**Field-level validation** (State 2):
- Required fields that extraction left empty: Show amber highlight border `#F59E0B` with helper text "We couldn't extract this from your brief â€” please fill it in"
- Required fields that extraction populated: Normal style, but still editable
- All fields validate on blur and before Generate button enables

#### Input Fields (shared across both states)

**Text input (single line)**:
- Height: 44px
- Border: 1px `#D1D5DB`, border-radius 8px
- Focus: Border `#2563EB`, ring `0 0 0 2px rgba(37,99,235,0.2)`
- Placeholder: 14px `#9CA3AF`
- Value text: 16px `#111827`
- Label: 14px medium `#374151`, 6px margin-bottom

**Textarea**:
- Same styling as text input but multi-row
- Row count specified per field (3, 4, or 6 rows)
- Auto-expand up to max 12 rows as user types (optional enhancement)

**Dropdown (Country selector)**:
- Same styling as text input
- Chevron icon right-aligned
- Options: Searchable dropdown. Pre-populated with major markets (US, UK, AU, NZ, CA, DE, FR, etc.)

**Helper text**:
- Below input, 13px regular, `#6B7280`
- Used sparingly â€” only where the field needs clarification

#### File Upload Area (Stimulus â€” in State 2)
- **Container**: Dashed border 2px `#D1D5DB`, border-radius 8px, padding 24px, text-centered
- **Drag hover state**: Border `#2563EB`, background `#EFF6FF`
- **Upload icon**: Cloud-upload outline icon, 32px, `#9CA3AF`
- **Primary text**: "Upload files or drag & drop" â€” 14px medium
- **Secondary text**: "Images, PDF, text â€” Max 5 files, 10MB each" â€” 13px `#9CA3AF`
- **After upload**: File chips appear below upload area. Each chip: filename + file size + [Ã—] remove button

#### Competitor Inputs
- **Layout**: Vertical stack of single-line text inputs
- **Pre-populated**: If extraction found competitors, fields are pre-filled
- **Default (no extraction)**: 3 empty inputs shown
- **"+ Add competitor"**: Text button below last input. Adds another input (max 6)
- **Empty inputs**: Are ignored on submission

#### LOI Note (Setup Page)
- The setup page no longer has a tier selector â€” it shows a simple informational note that LOI will be adjustable in the editor after generation
- **Style**: Light info box, `#F0F9FF` background, `#2563EB` left border 3px, padding 16px
- **Content**: Brief explanation + a miniature visual hint of the slider (static, non-interactive)

#### Methodology Preview (State 2, optional enhancement)
- **Visibility**: Appears in State 2 if extraction identified methodologies. Otherwise hidden.
- **Layout**: Row of small skill badges (pill-shaped, with icon and name). Read-only.
- **Style**: Each badge: `#EFF6FF` background, `#2563EB` text, border-radius 16px, padding 6px 12px
- **Info note**: "â„¹ï¸ These methodologies were selected based on your research objective. You can adjust the survey after generation." â€” 13px `#6B7280`
- **If not implemented for MVP**: Omit this section. The user will see the methodology reflected in the generated survey structure.

#### Generate Button (State 2)
- **Style**: Large primary button, full width of content area (720px max), height 52px
- **Label**: "Generate Survey â†’" â€” 16px semibold white
- **Background**: `#2563EB`, hover `#1D4ED8`
- **Disabled state**: When required fields are empty â€” `#D1D5DB` background, `#9CA3AF` text, no hover effect
- **Below button**: Helper text "â±ï¸ Generation typically takes 15-30 seconds" â€” 13px `#9CA3AF`

#### Generation Progress State (State 2)
- **Replaces**: The generate button area. The form above becomes read-only (slightly dimmed, inputs non-interactive).
- **Container**: White, border 1px `#E5E7EB`, border-radius 12px, padding 32px, centered
- **Progress bar**: 8px height, blue fill, step-based
- **Step list**: Vertical list of generation steps:
  1. "Extracting research objectives" (extract_brief.py)
  2. "Selecting methodologies: [skill names]" (skill selection)
  3. "Generating survey questions" (generate_survey.py)
  4. "Running validation checks" (validators)
- **On completion**: Brief green success state (1-2 sec), then auto-navigate to Editor page

#### Error State
- If generation fails (validation errors, etc.):
```
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚                                                          â”‚
â”‚  âŒ Generation encountered issues                        â”‚
â”‚                                                          â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Brief is too vague â€” add more detail about what       â”‚
â”‚    decisions this research needs to inform               â”‚
â”‚  â€¢ Could not determine target methodology from the       â”‚
â”‚    objective described                                   â”‚
â”‚                                                          â”‚
â”‚  [Try Again]   [Edit Brief]                              â”‚
â”‚                                                          â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
```

### Data Model (Brief / Setup)

**Raw brief input** (State 1 â†’ sent to extraction):

```json
{
  "raw_brief": {
    "text": "string (full pasted brief text)",
    "source_file": {
      "filename": "string or null",
      "type": "string (pdf/docx/txt) or null",
      "url": "string or null"
    }
  }
}
```

**Extraction output** (populates State 2 fields):

```json
{
  "extraction": {
    "confidence": "number (0-1, overall extraction confidence)",
    "fields": {
      "name": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "objective": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "category": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "target_audience": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "market": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "stimulus_description": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": true },
      "competitors": { "value": ["string"], "extracted": true },
      "specific_questions": { "value": "string or null", "extracted": false },
      "suggested_methodologies": ["string (skill names)"]
    }
  }
}
```

Each field has an `extracted` boolean â€” this drives the `[âœ¨ AI]` badge display. When the user edits a field, `extracted` flips to `false` for that field.

**Final brief** (State 2 â†’ sent to generation pipeline):

```json
{
  "project": {
    "id": "string (uuid, auto-generated)",
    "name": "string",
    "status": "draft",
    "created_at": "datetime",
    "updated_at": "datetime"
  },
  "brief": {
    "raw_text": "string (original pasted brief â€” preserved for reference)",
    "objective": "string",
    "category": "string",
    "target_audience": "string",
    "market": "string (country code)",
    "stimulus": {
      "text_description": "string or null",
      "files": [
        {
          "filename": "string",
          "type": "string (image/pdf/text)",
          "url": "string (uploaded file path)"
        }
      ]
    },
    "competitors": ["string"],
    "specific_questions": "string or null",
    "loi_tier": "quick | standard | deep"
  }
}
```

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] State 1: User can paste a brief into the large textarea
- [ ] State 1: User can upload a PDF/Word/text brief file that populates the textarea
- [ ] State 1: "Extract Brief" button triggers LLM extraction and shows progress
- [ ] State 1: "Fill in manually" link skips extraction and shows State 2 with empty fields
- [ ] State 2: All fields populated by extraction display `[âœ¨ AI]` badge
- [ ] State 2: `[âœ¨ AI]` badge disappears when user manually edits a field
- [ ] State 2: Fields extraction couldn't populate show amber highlight with helper text
- [ ] State 2: Original brief is preserved in collapsible banner with "Re-extract" and "Edit original" actions
- [ ] State 2: All required fields validate before Generate button enables
- [ ] State 2: LOI info note displays correctly (non-interactive, informational)
- [ ] State 2: File upload (stimulus) accepts drag-and-drop and file picker
- [ ] State 2: Competitor inputs can be added (up to 6) and removed
- [ ] State 2: Generate button triggers generation pipeline with progress display
- [ ] Generation progress shows real-time step updates
- [ ] Successful generation auto-navigates to Editor with survey loaded
- [ ] Generation errors display clearly with actionable guidance
- [ ] Brief data persists â€” returning to setup from editor shows State 2 with previously entered/extracted data
- [ ] Country dropdown is searchable

